cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image segmentation using deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNN) and conditional random fields (CRF). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep feature learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of CRF suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset and experiments with several benchmark datasets, indicating a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
